so today were auditions, and i hated it. 

So normally with dave we would have one day where we would sing solo, and then the next day we would do scenes.

Well this year since dave is gone matt demko is our new director and he had it so we go in as pairs, and we sing first and then do a cold reading of a scene. 

I HATE COLD READINGS.

plus, unfortunetly, i didn't get to go till 5pm. So basically i didn't really care going in, so guess who is going to be in the goddamn company.

I hate it.

Friday -- Meadowbrook
Saturday -- Dad's work
Sunday -- Meadowbrook.

Okay now that I've gotten that out of the way...let me tell you a little about a fellow at Meadowbrook. His name is Aaron, and he's 35...and he's funny, and nice, but....So he works at the icecream stand across the way from us, and we talk all the time, and it used to be normal, but now....

...well lets just say that he's buying me flowers, and asking to go to concerts with me, and he's blown me some kisses.

Yeahhhh. I think he tested the waters a little cause he was like "So would your boyfriend be mad if i bought you flowers?" and i was like "uhh..yeah." lol...but i think today he's getting me them anyways! I'll keep you updated on sketchy stalker.

So...speaking of that boyfriend of mine....:-( I miss him. I haven't seen him in like, forever, and...i feel like we're drifting and I hate it and I don't know what to do. Wednesday we're spending all day together, i hope...maybe that will make me feel better.

I think i'm going to take him to gunstock and go horseback riding:-) and then maybe a little mini golf, or something:-) 

I love him so much.

So i think I'm going to call Patricia and ask her to take me off the waitlist for New Zealand. I've gotten over the fact that I'm not accepted...Im still a little shocked and disappointed, but...I've pretty much accepted it. And i think maybe I'll just go abroad during college or something...I donno. But i am contemplating having her take me off the list.

Speaking of colleges...COLLEGE SEARCHING SUCKS. Okay so the one school I really really really really really want to get into is like...a "never-gonna-happen" sorta thing. 

Yeah, its Yale.

Well, whatever, i'm visiting Yale next week...along with BU, and probably Williams and Suffolk. And then I'm flying out to Michigan and going to U of M, M State, and Albian.  And then I'm going to NY and going to all the colleges there....and then I'm finding random colleges in CA and if i want to go visit then I'll go there too.

JESUS!
